tras". Lectura y consumo se conjugan en estas páginas para ofrecer otras formas de ciudadanía a sujetos que, en su condición periférica como mujeres e inmigrantes, habitaban los márgenes de la modernidad y de la vida moderna norteamericana.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Spanish, Castilian.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aHispanic American newspaperszNew York (State)zNew York. 0aHispanic American periodicalszNew York (State)zNew York. 0aHispanic American womenzNew York (State)zNew York. 4aCultural Studies. 4aGeneral. 7aART / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2019z9783110605747oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertVervuert Complete eBook-Package 2018z9783110606768oZDB-207-IBV40uhttps://doi.org/10.31819/978395487925040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783954879250423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783954879250.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_AD  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-207-IBVb2018  aZDB-23-DADb2019  aZDB-23-DGGb2019